cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper describes a deep neural network for predicting brain segmentations from MRI volumes, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of Bayesian methods for uncertainty estimation and the novel spike-and-slab dropout-based variational inference approach suggest a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper also discusses the potential for natural language processing (cs.CL) applications of the proposed method.
